#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:0.3"
msgid "Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Suspension"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:0.4"
msgid "Vihāra­kāra­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "7. The training rule on building dwellings"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.156, pts-vp-en1.266, pts-cs-bu-ss7.1, ms1V_1512 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato channassa upaṭṭhāko gahapati āyasmantaṃ channaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "At that time a lay person who was a supporter of Venerable Channa said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.3"
msgid "“vihāravatthuṃ, bhante, jānāhi ayyassa vihāraṃ kārāpessāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, please find a site for a dwelling, and I’ll have one built for you.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā channo vihāravatthuṃ sodhento aññataraṃ cetiyarukkhaṃ chedāpesi gāmapūjitaṃ nigamapūjitaṃ nagarapūjitaṃ jana­pada­pūjitaṃ raṭṭhapūjitaṃ."
msgstr "While Venerable Channa was clearing a site for that dwelling, he had a tree felled that had served as a shrine and that was revered by village, town, district, and kingdom."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.5"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.6"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā cetiyarukkhaṃ chedāpessanti gāmapūjitaṃ nigamapūjitaṃ nagarapūjitaṃ jana­pada­pūjitaṃ raṭṭhapūjitaṃ."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics have such a tree felled?"

#. VAR: viheṭhentī → viheṭhessanti (katthaci)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.7"
msgid "Ekindriyaṃ samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jīvaṃ viheṭhentī”ti."
msgstr "They are hurting life with one faculty.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_1513 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.8"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the criticism of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.9"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.267
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.10"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.11"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo cetiyarukkhaṃ chedāpessati gāmapūjitaṃ … pe … raṭṭhapūjitan”ti."
msgstr "Venerable Channa in the same manner."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_1514 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.12"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ channaṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing Venerable Channa in various ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.13"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, cetiyarukkhaṃ chedāpesi gāmapūjitaṃ … pe … raṭṭhapūjitan”ti?"
msgstr "He said, “Is it true, Channa, that you had a tree felled that had served as a shrine and that was revered by village, town, district, and kingdom?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.14"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.15"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.16"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, cetiyarukkhaṃ chedāpessasi gāmapūjitaṃ nigamapūjitaṃ nagarapūjitaṃ jana­pada­pūjitaṃ raṭṭhapūjitaṃ."
msgstr "“… Foolish man, how can you do such a thing?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.17"
msgid "Jīvasaññino hi, moghapurisa, manussā rukkhasmiṃ."
msgstr "People perceive trees as living beings."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

# NOTE: I have rendered _sassāmikaṃ_ as “with a sponsoring owner.” The word _sāmika_ generally means “owner,” and there seems to be no reason why that should not also be the meaning here. However, although the monk does not own the dwelling, he is still the builder and the intended user once the building is finished. To indicate this, I have added the word “sponsoring.”
#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.20"
msgid "“Mahallakaṃ pana bhikkhunā vihāraṃ kārayamānena sassāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ bhikkhū abhinetabbā vatthudesanāya."
msgstr "‘When a monk builds a large dwelling with a sponsoring owner and intended for himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.21"
msgid "Tehi bhikkhūhi vatthu desetabbaṃ anārambhaṃ saparikkamanaṃ."
msgstr "he must get monks to approve a site where no harm will be done and which has a space on all sides."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:1.22"
msgid "Sārambhe ce bhikkhu vatthusmiṃ aparikkamane mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kāreyya bhikkhū vā anabhineyya vatthudesanāya, saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "If a monk builds a large dwelling on a site where harm will be done and which lacks a space on all sides, or he does not get monks to approve the site, he commits an offense entailing suspension.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-ss7.2, ms1V_1516
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.1"
msgid "Mahallako nāma"
msgstr "A large dwelling:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.2"
msgid "vihāro sassāmiko vuccati."
msgstr "one with a sponsoring owner is what is meant."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_1517
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.3"
msgid "Vihāro nāma"
msgstr "Dwelling:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.4"
msgid "ullitto vā hoti avalitto vā ullittāvalitto vā."
msgstr "a wattle and daub dwelling."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, pts-vp-en1.268, ms1V_1518
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.5"
msgid "Kārayamānenāti"
msgstr "Builds:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.6"
msgid "karonto vā kārāpento vā."
msgstr "building it himself or getting someone else to build it."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_1519
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.7"
msgid "Sassāmikanti"
msgstr "With a sponsoring owner:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.8"
msgid "añño koci sāmiko hoti itthī vā puriso vā gahaṭṭho vā pabbajito vā."
msgstr "there is another owner, either a woman or a man, either a lay person or one gone forth."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_1520
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.9"
msgid "Attuddesanti"
msgstr "Intended for himself:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.10"
msgid "attano atthāya."
msgstr "for his own use."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_1521
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.11"
msgid "Bhikkhū abhinetabbā vatthudesanāyāti"
msgstr "He must get monks to approve a site:"

#. HTML: </span></p><div class="gloss"><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.12"
msgid "tena vihārakārakena bhikkhunā vihāravatthuṃ sodhetvā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "The monk who is building a dwelling should clear a site, then approach the Order, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.13"
msgid "“ahaṃ, bhante, mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kattukāmo sassāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr "“Venerables, I wish to build a large dwelling with a sponsoring owner and intended for myself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.14"
msgid "Sohaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ vihāra­vatthu­o­loka­naṃ yācāmī”ti."
msgstr "I request the Order to inspect the site for the dwelling.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.15"
msgid "Dutiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "He should make his request a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.16"
msgid "Tatiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.17"
msgid "Sace sabbo saṃgho ussahati vihāravatthuṃ oloketuṃ sabbena saṃghena oloketabbaṃ."
msgstr "If the whole Order is able to inspect the site, they should all go."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.18"
msgid "No ce sabbo saṃgho ussahati vihāravatthuṃ oloketuṃ,"
msgstr "If the whole Order is not able to inspect the site,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.19"
msgid "ye tattha honti bhikkhū byattā paṭibalā sārambhaṃ anārambhaṃ saparikkamanaṃ aparikkamanaṃ jānituṃ te yācitvā sammannitabbā."
msgstr "then those monks there who are competent and capable—who know where harm will be done and where no harm will be done, and who understands the meaning of space on all sides and a lacks a space on all sides—should be asked and then appointed."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.20"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbā."
msgstr "“And, monks, they should be appointed in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.21"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. HTML: </p><div class="kamma"><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_1522 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.22"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.23"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kattukāmo sassāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr "Monk so-and-so wishes to build a large dwelling with a sponsoring owner and intended for himself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.24"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ vihāra­vatthu­o­loka­naṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is requesting the Order to inspect the site for the dwelling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.25"
msgid "Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū sammanneyya itthannāmassa bhikkhuno vihāravatthuṃ oloketuṃ."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should appoint monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so to inspect the site."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.26"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_1523 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.27"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.28"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kattukāmo sassāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr "Monk so-and-so wishes to build a large dwelling with a sponsoring owner and intended for himself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.29"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ vihāra­vatthu­o­loka­naṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is requesting the Order to inspect the site for the dwelling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.30"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū sammannati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno vihāravatthuṃ oloketuṃ."
msgstr "The Order is appointing monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so to inspect the site."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.31"
msgid "Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa ca itthannāmassa ca bhikkhūnaṃ sammuti itthannāmassa bhikkhuno vihāravatthuṃ oloketuṃ, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr "Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so to inspect the site for the dwelling should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.32"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should speak up."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_1524 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.33"
msgid "Sammatā saṃghena itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca bhikkhū itthannāmassa bhikkhuno vihāravatthuṃ oloketuṃ."
msgstr "Monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so have been appointed by the Order to inspect the site for the dwelling of monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.34"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.35"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’"

#. HTML: </p></div><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_1525 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.36"
msgid "Tehi sammatehi bhikkhūhi tattha gantvā vihāravatthu oloketabbaṃ;"
msgstr "The appointed monks should go and inspect the site for the dwelling"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.37"
msgid "sārambhaṃ anārambhaṃ saparikkamanaṃ aparikkamanaṃ jānitabbaṃ."
msgstr "to find out if any harm will be done and if it has a space on all sides."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.38"
msgid "Sace sārambhaṃ hoti aparikkamanaṃ,"
msgstr "If harm will be done and it lacks a space on all sides, they should say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.39"
msgid "“māyidha karī”ti vattabbo."
msgstr "‘Don’t build here.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.40"
msgid "Sace anārambhaṃ hoti saparikkamanaṃ, saṃghassa ārocetabbaṃ—"
msgstr "If no harm will be done and it has a space on all sides, they should inform the Order:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.41"
msgid "“anārambhaṃ saparikkamanan”ti."
msgstr "‘No harm will be done and it has a space on all sides.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.42"
msgid "Tena vihārakārakena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "The monk who is building the dwelling should then approach the Order, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.43"
msgid "“ahaṃ, bhante, mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kattukāmo sassāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, I wish to build a large dwelling with a sponsoring owner and intended for myself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.44"
msgid "Sohaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ vihāra­vatthu­desanaṃ yācāmī”ti."
msgstr "I request the Order to approve the site for the dwelling.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.45"
msgid "Dutiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "He should make his request a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.46"
msgid "Tatiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.47"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should then inform the Order:"

#. HTML: </span></p><div class="kamma"><p>
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_1526 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.48"
msgid "“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.49"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kattukāmo sassāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr "Monk so-and-so wishes to build a large dwelling with a sponsoring owner and intended for himself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.50"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ vihāra­vatthu­desanaṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is requesting the Order to approve the site for the dwelling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.51"
msgid "Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno vihāravatthuṃ deseyya."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should approve the site."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.52"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_1527 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.53"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.54"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu mahallakaṃ vihāraṃ kattukāmo sassāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr "Monk so-and-so wishes to build a large dwelling with a sponsoring owner and intended for himself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.55"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ vihāra­vatthu­desanaṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is requesting the Order to approve the site for the dwelling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.56"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno vihāravatthuṃ deseti."
msgstr "The Order approves the site for the dwelling of monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.57"
msgid "Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno vihāra­vatthussa desanā, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr "Any monk who approves of approving the site for the dwelling should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.58"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should speak up."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_1528 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.59"
msgid "Desitaṃ saṃghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno vihāravatthu."
msgstr "The site for the dwelling of monk so-and-so has been approved by the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.60"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.61"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. HTML: </p></div></div><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_1529
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.62"
msgid "Sārambhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Where harm will be done:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss7:2.63"
msgid "kipillikānaṃ vā āsayo hoti, upacikānaṃ vā āsayo hoti, undūrānaṃ vā … pe …"
msgstr "it is the abode of ants, termites, rats,"

